isPower of two or not

Given an integer N, Find whether it is possible to write in terms of 2 power or not.

*Hint: Try to solve without using functions, Loops.

Input Format

First line contains an integer represents no of test cases T.

Next T lines contains value N.

Constraints

1<= T <= 3,000,000

1<= N <= 9,000,000,000,000,000,000

Output Format

Print Yes if it is possible to write in terms of 2 Power.

Print No if it is not possible to write.

Sample Input 0

2
2
4
Sample Output 0

Yes
Yes
Sample Input 1

3
2
4
6
Sample Output 1

Yes
Yes
No

Solution:

#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
long long int n,t;
    scanf("%lld",&t);
    while(t>0)
        {
        scanf("%lld",&n);
     if((n & (n - 1)) == 0)
     {
   printf("Yes\n");
      }
      else{
         printf("No\n");
          }
            t--;
    }
}
